---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-coverage', text: 'Plans and Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pros-and-cons', text: 'Pros and Cons', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims-and-service', text: 'Claims and Service', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who It\'s For', level: 2 },
  { id: 'alternatives', text: 'Alternatives to Consider', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Allianz vs Cigna', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Allianz vs BUPA', href: '/compare/allianz-care-vs-bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz vs AXA', href: '/compare/axa-global-vs-allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Best Expat Insurance', href: '/best/expat-health-insurance' },
  { title: 'Allianz in Spain', href: '/countries/spain/insurance/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Allianz in France', href: '/countries/france/insurance/allianz-care' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'limit', header: 'Annual Limit' },
  { key: 'maternity', header: 'Maternity' },
  { key: 'bestFor', header: 'Best For' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Base', limit: '$1.35 million', maternity: 'Add-on', bestFor: 'Essential coverage' },
  { plan: 'Enhanced', limit: '$2.7 million', maternity: 'Included', bestFor: 'Comprehensive care' },
  { plan: 'Signature', limit: '$5 million', maternity: 'Included + Fertility', bestFor: 'Premium coverage' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Allianz Care Review"
  description="In-depth review of Allianz Care international health insurance. Coverage options, pricing, pros and cons for expats."
  headline="Allianz Care International Health Insurance Review"
  subheadline="A detailed look at Allianz Care's plans, pricing, and whether they might be right for your expat needs."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Allianz Care Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care is the international health insurance arm of Allianz Partners, part of Allianz SE—one of the world's largest insurance and financial services companies. With an A+ Superior rating from A.M. Best, they bring significant financial backing to the expat insurance market.
  </p>
  <p>
    The company offers international health coverage for expats, digital nomads, students, and families living abroad for 12 months or more. They're known for flexible plan options and a massive global provider network.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Quick Facts</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
      <li><strong>Parent Company:</strong> Allianz SE (Munich, Germany)</li>
      <li><strong>Financial Rating:</strong> A+ Superior (A.M. Best)</li>
      <li><strong>Network Providers:</strong> 2 million+</li>
      <li><strong>Countries Covered:</strong> 200+ territories</li>
      <li><strong>Plan Types:</strong> Base, Enhanced, Signature</li>
      <li><strong>Age Limit:</strong> Up to 75 to enroll</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Personalized Quote"
    description="See what Allianz Care would cost for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="plans-and-coverage">Plans and Coverage</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers three main plan tiers—Base, Enhanced, and Signature—each with increasing coverage limits and benefits. All plans include inpatient care as a foundation, with optional add-ons for outpatient and dental coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Core Coverage (All Plans)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Hospital stays with private room accommodation</li>
    <li>Surgical procedures and specialist treatment</li>
    <li>Cancer treatment (oncology covered up to plan maximum)</li>
    <li>Medical repatriation</li>
    <li>Emergency evacuation</li>
    <li>Health and wellbeing checks</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Enhanced and Signature Extras</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> Routine pregnancy, childbirth, and complications (12-month waiting period)</li>
    <li><strong>Bariatric surgery:</strong> Weight loss surgery (24-month waiting period)</li>
    <li><strong>Fertility treatment:</strong> Up to $9,450 on Signature plan (12-month waiting period)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Optional Add-Ons</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, diagnostics, prescriptions, eye exams, glasses/contacts</li>
    <li><strong>Dental:</strong> Preventive and restorative dental care</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Geographic Coverage Options</h3>
  <p>
    Choose your coverage area based on where you'll be living:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Worldwide (including USA)</li>
    <li>Worldwide excluding USA</li>
    <li>Europe</li>
    <li>Africa</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Note:</strong> Allianz Care is not available if you reside in Brazil, Dubai/UAE, Germany, Ireland, Iran, North Korea, Russia, or countries under international sanctions.
  </p>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care pricing depends on your age, plan tier, deductible choice, coverage area, and optional add-ons. Excluding US coverage reduces premiums significantly.
  </p>

  <h3>Estimated Monthly Premiums (Worldwide excluding USA)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Age 25: €95-110/month ($100-120)</li>
    <li>Age 35: €110-140/month ($120-150)</li>
    <li>Age 45: €135-180/month ($145-195)</li>
    <li>Age 55: €220-300/month ($240-325)</li>
    <li>Age 65: €350-400/month ($380-435)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <em>Estimates based on Enhanced plan with moderate deductible. Actual prices vary.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Ways to Reduce Premiums</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Up to 60% savings with €10,000 deductible</li>
    <li><strong>Exclude US coverage:</strong> Significant savings if you won't visit the US</li>
    <li><strong>Pay annually:</strong> Avoid 3-5% surcharges for monthly/quarterly payments</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> Europe-only plans cost less than worldwide</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Payment Options</h3>
  <p>
    Pay annually (0% surcharge), half-yearly (3%), quarterly (4%), or monthly (5%). Bank transfer and debit card accepted; monthly payments require direct debit.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="See Your Actual Price"
    description="Get a quote based on your age, location, and coverage needs."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="pros-and-cons">Pros and Cons</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Pros</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Massive provider network (2M+ worldwide)</li>
        <li>Strong financial backing (Allianz SE)</li>
        <li>Flexible deductible options (up to 60% savings)</li>
        <li>Excellent oncology coverage</li>
        <li>24/7 emergency assistance included</li>
        <li>Telemedicine Hub for remote consultations</li>
        <li>Expat Assistance Program (counseling, legal referrals)</li>
        <li>Direct billing at network hospitals</li>
        <li>No waiting periods for core coverage</li>
        <li>Enroll up to age 75</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3">Cons</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-800">
        <li>Mixed customer reviews on claims handling</li>
        <li>Pre-existing conditions require full underwriting</li>
        <li>12-month maternity waiting period</li>
        <li>Can't cancel mid-year (after 30-day cooling off)</li>
        <li>Not available in several countries (Germany, Ireland, UAE, Brazil)</li>
        <li>Monthly payments have 5% surcharge</li>
        <li>Some reports of slow claims processing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="claims-and-service">Claims and Service</h2>

  <h3>Filing Claims</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care processes claims through their online portal and mobile app. According to the company, 74% of claims are processed within 24 hours, and most within 48 hours.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Online claims submission via MyHealth portal</li>
    <li>Mobile app for claims and ID cards</li>
    <li>Direct settlement with network hospitals for inpatient care</li>
    <li>Reimbursement for out-of-network care</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care provides 24/7 emergency assistance and customer support. They also offer:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>MediLine Medical Advice Service (speak with medical professionals)</li>
    <li>Telemedicine Hub for remote consultations</li>
    <li>Expat Assistance Program (counseling, legal and financial referrals)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Customer Reviews</h3>
  <p>
    Customer experiences vary. While some praise the coverage and provider network, others report frustrations with claims handling and customer service responsiveness. Common complaints include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Difficulty getting claims approved for certain conditions</li>
    <li>Strict interpretation of pre-existing condition exclusions</li>
    <li>Inconsistent service quality</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    As with any insurer, document everything and understand your coverage before you need to use it.
  </p>

  <h3>Pre-Existing Conditions</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care uses full medical underwriting. When you apply, you'll disclose your health history and they'll decide what to cover. Pre-existing conditions may be:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Covered with limitations</li>
    <li>Excluded temporarily</li>
    <li>Excluded permanently</li>
    <li>Subject to premium loading</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Be thorough and honest on your application—undisclosed conditions can result in claim denials.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who It's For</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care may be a good fit if you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Want a large, established provider with global reach</li>
    <li>Prefer flexible deductible options to control costs</li>
    <li>Need coverage in Europe, Africa, or Asia (non-US)</li>
    <li>Value included extras like telemedicine and expat assistance</li>
    <li>Are under 75 and in reasonably good health</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    It may not be ideal if you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Live in Germany, Ireland, UAE, or Brazil (not available)</li>
    <li>Have significant pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>Need maximum flexibility to cancel mid-year</li>
    <li>Prioritize customer service ratings above all else</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="alternatives">Alternatives to Consider</h2>
  <p>
    If Allianz Care doesn't seem like the right fit, consider these alternatives:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Larger provider network, strong customer service reputation. <a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our review</a></li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Premium option with comprehensive benefits and strong service</li>
    <li><strong>IMG Global:</strong> Budget-friendly with high-deductible options</li>
    <li><strong>Aetna International:</strong> Good choice for seamless US coverage integration</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <a href="/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care">See our Cigna vs Allianz comparison</a>
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Compare?"
    description="See how Allianz Care compares to other options for your needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This review is for informational purposes only. Plan details, pricing, and availability change frequently. We are not affiliated with Allianz Care and are not insurance brokers. Verify all information directly with Allianz Care before purchasing. Coverage restrictions and excluded countries may have changed since this review was written.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
